Deflect Spells															CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ki Pool	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deflect Arrows,Improved Unarmed Strike																																																																											PRESTAT:2,DEX=13,WIS=13																					DESC:Prevent a spell with a ranged attack roll from hitting you.																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.59											BENEFIT:You must have at least one hand free to use this feat. 1/round, when you would normally be hit with a ranged attack from a spell, extraordinary natural weapon, spell-like ability, or supernatural ability, you may spend 1 point from your ki pool to deflect it so that you take no damage from it. You must be aware of the attack and not flat-footed. Attempting to deflect a magic ranged attack doesn't count as an action. Only spells and abilities that require a ranged attack roll can be deflected with this feat.
