Guerilla Tactics															CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																	PRECSKILL:1,Stealth																																																																																					DESC:Plan an ambush, giving your allies bonuses for 1-3 rnds.																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.62											BENEFIT:You can form an ambush plan for any combat area you have information about in advance. You must either observe the conditions of the prospective battlefield personally, or receive a detailed scouting report. Forming a plan takes 1 minute, but if the information you base it on is inaccurate (or changes) your plan grants no bonus. Your plan grants a bonus to you and any allies you have briefed on the plan based on your Stealth check: +1 if 20 or less; +2 if 21-30; or +3 if 31 or more. This bonus begins in the 1st round of combat, and is reduced by 1 at the end of your turn on the 2nd round of combat, and each round thereafter. The bonus applies to attack rolls, saving throws, and Stealth checks.
Head Butt																CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Toughness																																																																																							PRESTAT:1,CON=13																						DESC:Gain a natural weapon attack.											TEMPLATE:CHOOSE:Head Butt ~ Small|Head Butt ~ Medium|Head Butt ~ Large																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.62											BENEFIT:You gain a head butt natural attack. If you have an unarmed attack that deals more damage, you may choose to deal that damage instead. If you damage a foe with this natural weapon, you take 1/4 of the damage you inflict (damage reduction does not modify this damage). You can use this natural attack without penalty even if your hands and feet are bound, or if you are in a grapple.
Improved Catch Off-Guard													CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Catch Off-Guard																																																																																																														DESC:Constantly surprise foes with improvised weapons.																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.63											BENEFIT:Foes (even armed foes) are flat-footed against attacks you make with an improvised weapon. At the end of each round as a free action, a foe may make a Sense Motive check opposed by your Bluff check. If the foe is successful, it stops being flat-footed by any improvised weapon attack you make for 24 hours. Your improvised weapon attacks threaten a critical on an attack roll of 19-20.
Knife Trick																CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																																																																																																									DESC:Draw and attack with a light weapon using Sleight of Hand.																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.63											BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can draw a light weapon and attack one target with it. Rather than make a standard attack roll, make a Sleight of Hand check. If your skill check exceeds your target's AC, your attack hits. If your skill check also exceeds a DC of 10 + the target's base attack bonus + the target's Wisdom modifier (or 10 + the target's Sense Motive bonus, whichever is higher), your target is also denied its Dexterity bonus to AC against this attack. Any given target may be the target of your knife trick only once per day.
