Set Up																CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.AttackOption	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Subtle																																																																																																																DESC:Make an attack to draw a foe off-guard, giving allies +2 to attacks.																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.68											BENEFIT:As a standard action, make a melee attack with a +2 circumstance bonus against one foe. If your attack hits, you deal no damage and your foe thinks you simply missed. In fact, in order to dodge your attack, your foe has moved himself into a more vulnerable position, and all your allies have +2 circumstance bonuses to melee attacks against that foe until the beginning of your next turn.
Shield Specialization		KEY:Shield Specialization ~ SGGAH							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Shield Focus																											PREMULT:1,[PREPROFWITHSHIELD:3,TYPE.Buckler,TYPE.Light,TYPE.Heavy],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Shield Proficiency]																																																																	DESC:Gain bonuses when fighting defensively.																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.69											BENEFIT:Whenever you fight defensively or take the full defense action and you are using a shield, you double the normal bonus to AC granted by the maneuver. Additionally, you make take the Deflect Arrows feat even if you do not meet its normal prerequisites. However, rather than having one hand free to use the Deflect Arrows feat, you must have a shield.
Smash					KEY:Smash ~ SGGAH										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Power Attack																																																																																							PRESTAT:1,STR=13		PRETOTALAB:1																		DESC:Add your armor bonus to Strength checks to break things.																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.69											BENEFIT:If you charge into an object (including doors and walls), you may add your armor bonus and shield bonus to a Strength check to attempt to break it. If you successfully Bull Rush a foe, you can push him back an additional 5 ft. for every 5 points of armor bonus you have.
Sucker Punch															CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.AttackOption	PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deceitful,Improved Unarmed Attack,Quick Draw																																																																																																										DESC:Stun or knock out a foe you punch from surprise.																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.70											BENEFIT:If you attack a flat-footed foe in the surprise round with an unarmed attack and successfully strike and damage the target, that foe must make a Fortitude save (DC %1) or be stunned for 1 round. If the target fails this save by 5 or more, it is instead unconscious for 1d4 rounds (creatures that are immune to critical hits and those that need not sleep are stunned for an additional 1d4 rounds).|10+TL/2+STR
Surprise Attack															CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.AttackOption																														PRECSKILL:1,Stealth																																																																																					DESC:Charge an unsuspecting target without being noticed.																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.71											BENEFIT:When you are unobserved, you may take a full-round action to charge a single target that is unaware of you. You make a Stealth check opposed by your opponent's Perception check. If your check succeeds, your target is unaware of you until after the attack at the end of your charge (other creatures may notice you normally). The target is denied its Dexterity bonus against this attack.
Takedown																CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Athletic																																																																																																																DESC:Make attacks that can hit multiple targets.																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.71											BENEFIT:If you make a weapon attack (including natural weapon and unarmed strikes) that deals enough damage to knock a target unconscious or dead, once per round you get an immediate extra attack against another creature with the same weapon and at the same attack bonus. If the initial attack was a melee attack, your second attack must target another foe within reach. If the initial attack was a ranged attack, your second target must be in line with and beyond your first target. You cannot take a 5-ft. step before taking this extra attack.
Touchi																CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.AttackOption																																																																																														PRESTAT:1,DEX=13		PRETOTALAB:1													DEFINE:ToucheBonus|0		DESC:Take a penalty to damage to gain a bonus to attack rolls.																		ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Touchi (1H or Light + off-hand empty)|Touchi (Otherwise)																																													BONUS:VAR|ToucheBonus|1+BAB/4																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.71											BENEFIT:You can choose to take a -%1 penalty to all weapon damage and combat maneuver checks to gain a +%1 to all melee weapon attack rolls. This bonus to attack rolls is increased by an additional +1 if you are fighting with a one-handed or light weapon in one hand, and have nothing in your other hand. You must choose to use this feat before making any attack rolls, and its effects last until your next turn. The bonus does not apply to touch attacks or effects that do not deal hit point damage.|ToucheBonus
