Battle Mage									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General											PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=5																																						PRESTAT:1,STR=13									DESC:Gain spells you can only use if you've been in combat.							STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE												BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Battle Mage Spell|6										SOURCEPAGE:p.55	BENEFIT:You may select 6 battle mage spells to become part of your spell list. If you have limited spells known, you do not automatically know these spells, but you may learn three of them for only one spell slot towards your maximum spells known. Each time you successfully hit a foe with a weapon attack not augmented by a spell, you gain one battle mark. Any time you fail an attack roll, you lose one battle mark. You may spend a battle mark to cast one of your known selected spells by spending a spell slot of the same level or higher. Each day when you regain uses of your spells, you lose any unused battle marks.
Blood Magic									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General											PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=5																																																	DESC:Learn spells you can only cast after taking damage.							STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE												BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Blood Mage Spell|6										SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:You may select 6 blood mage spells to become part of your spell list. If you have limited spells known, you do not automatically know these spells, but you may learn three of them for only one spell slot towards your maximum spells known. Each time you take %1+ hp damage from a single blow or source, or have a -2 or greater penalty inflicted on you as a pain effect, you gain one blood mark. Any time you regain hit points through any method, you lose one blood mark. You may spend a blood mark to cast one of your known selected spells by spending a spell slot of the same level or higher. Each day when you regain uses of your spells, you lose any unused blood marks.|TL
Caustic Hex									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																									PRESPELLDESCRIPTOR:3,Acid=0																			DESC:Reduce an acid spell's save DC to gain a secondary effect.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.57	BENEFIT:You can cast spells that deal acid damage and allow a saving throw as caustic spells, creating a cloud of burning vapor around any target that fails its save. The save DC of the caustic spell is 1 lower than normal. The vapor lasts for 1 round for every 3 levels of the caustic spell (minimum 1 round). Targets engulfed in the vapor have difficulty seeing, hearing, or smelling targets, and treat all other creatures as having 20%% concealment for the duration. Targets with blindsense and those immune to acid damage are immune to this added effect.
Chill Hex									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																									PRESPELLDESCRIPTOR:3,Cold=0																			DESC:Reduce a cold spell's save DC to gain a secondary effect.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BENEFIT:You can cast spells that deal cold damage and allow a saving throw as chill spells, which reach colder temperatures and cause any target that fails its save to move more slowly. The save DC of the chill spell is 1 lower than normal. The chill effect lasts for a number of rounds equal to 1 + the level of the chill spell. Targets affected begin to shiver and develop a skin of frost, and have all their movement rates halved for the duration. Targets immune to critical hits or cold damage are immune to this added effect.
