Far Caster									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General.Magister																																																							PRETEXT:Spellcasting attribute 13			DESC:Increase your effective caster level for determining range.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.61	BENEFIT:When determining the maximum range of your spells, you treat your caster level as if it were two higher.
Jolt Hex									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																									PRESPELLDESCRIPTOR:3,Electricity=0																		DESC:Reduce an electricity spell's save DC to gain a secondary effect.																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.63	BENEFIT:You can cast spells that deal electricity damage and allow a saving throw as jolt spells, which linger on the body of a target that fails its save. The save DC of the jolt spell is 1 lower than normal. The jolt effect lasts for a number of rounds equal to the level of the jolt spell (minimum 1). Targets affected suffer muscle spasms, causing a -4 penalty to all Dex-based ability and skill checks, and a -2 penalty to all ranged attack rolls. Targets with Improved Evasion or immunity to electricity damage are immune to this added effect.
