Mounted Caster								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Mounted Combat																						PRESKILL:1,Ride=1																															DESC:Cast while riding without concentration checks.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.65	BENEFIT:You can have a mount move both before and after you cast a spell, and cast a spell while your mount takes a run action, without needing to make a concentration check. You gain a +2 bonus to any concentration check you are forced to make while mounted.
Necrothurge									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General											PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=5																																																	DESC:Learn spells you can only cast after killing someone.							STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE												BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Necrothurge Spell|6										SOURCEPAGE:p.66	BENEFIT:You may select 6 necrothurge spells to become part of your spell list. If you have limited spells known, you do not automatically know these spells, but you may learn three of them for only one spell slot towards your maximum spells known. Each time you kill a living creature with a CR of at least %1, you gain one death mark. You may spend a death mark to cast one of your known selected spells by spending a spell slot of the same level or higher. Each day when you regain uses of your spells, you lose any unused death marks.|TL-3
Plait Incantation								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General.Magister		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus		PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=1																																																	DESC:Ready to use a spell to increase another caster's spell power.																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.66	BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can ready an action to plait one of your spells into that of another spellcaster. When the allied spellcaster casts a spell, you take your readied action to cast your spell in response. Rather than have its normal effect, your spell grants your allied spellcaster a +2 enhancement bonus to his caster level for the spell that triggered your readied action. The spell you use to plait with your ally's must be within 2 levels of the spell cast by your ally, and cannot be a 0-level spell.
Scorch Hex									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																									PRESPELLDESCRIPTOR:3,Fire=0																			DESC:Reduce a fire spell's save DC to gain a secondary effect.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.67	BENEFIT:You can cast spells that deal fire damage and allow a saving throw as scorch spells, setting any target that fails its save on fire. The save DC of the scorch spell is 1 lower than normal. The fire burns until extinguished (as a standard action or by an ally making a DC 15+spell level Heal check). Burning targets take fire damage at the beginning of your turn every round depending on the level of the scorch spell (0-1st level: 1 point; 2nd-3rd level: 1d3 points; 4th-5th: 1d4 points; 6th+: 1d6 points). Targets with Improved Evasion and those immune to fire damage (or non-flammable) are immune to this added effect.
Secret Spell								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																															PRESKILL:2,Bluff=5,Spellcraft=5																												DESC:Cast a spell stealthily.																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BENEFIT:You may make a Spellcraft check to conceal the act of spellcasting from opponents observing you (+5 if the spell has no verbal component; -5 if the spell has a material component or focus). Your check is opposed each round of casting by the Perception check of each observer. Casting a spell secretly takes at least a full round action, even if the spell's normal casting time is less. If the spell has no listed visual or other sensory effects, any opponent who fails the opposed Perception check is unaware a spell has been cast; otherwise, observers become aware you have cast the spell once it takes effect, even if they failed their Perception check.
Sidewinder Hex								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																															PRESKILL:1,Bluff=3																														DESC:Cast a spell that fakes what target it's headed for.																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.69	BENEFIT:You can cast spells that deal damage as sidewinder spells, which give false visual cues as to their end destination. Such spells must have a casting time of 1 standard action or less, target one or more creatures (rather than an area), and either deal dice of damage or have a duration based on caster level. Casting the spell as a sidewinder hex takes a full-round action, and allows you to make a Bluff check opposed by the Sense Motive check of each target. Targets that fail the opposed check suffer a -2 penalty to their AC and saving throws against the sidewinder hex. However, the spell deals 1 point less damage per die (if it deals dice of damage) and has its duration halved (if it has a duration based on caster level).
