Signature Spell								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																			PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Mastery],[PREDOMAIN:1,ANY]																																		DESC:Sacrifice a prepared spell to cast your signature spell.								MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|ALL[KNOWN=YES]																										SOURCEPAGE:p.69	BENEFIT:You can channel stored spell energy into your signature spell even if you haven't prepared it ahead of time. (A signature spell must be one you have Spell Mastery with, or be from one of your domains.) You can cast your signature spell spontaneously by losing a prepared spell of the same level or higher.
Spell Bluff			KEY:Spell Bluff ~ SGGAH			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Secret Spell																						PRESKILL:2,Bluff=5,Spellcraft=5																												DESC:Fool observers about what spell you are casting.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.70	BENEFIT:You may make a Bluff check when spellcasting to fool observers into thinking you are casting a different spell (-5 if the spell has a material component or focus). Your check is opposed each round of casting by the Spellcraft check of each observer. You select what spell those failing their Spellcraft check believe you are casting (if this is not a spell you can cast you take a -5 penalty to your Bluff check). The effects of your spell may reveal your deception once it has been fully cast, but not until after it is too late for a foe to counterspell.
