Trickster Mage								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General											PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=5																																						PRESTAT:1,CHA=13									DESC:Learn spells you can only cast when you have deceived someone.					STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE												BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Trickster Mage Spell|6										SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BENEFIT:You may select 6 trickster mage spells to become part of your spell list. If you have limited spells known, you do not automatically know these spells, but you may learn three of them for only one spell slot towards your maximum spells known. Each time you make a successful Bluff check in a situation where you cannot take 10, you gain one duplicity mark. Any time you fail a Bluff, Disguise, or Linguistics (Forgery) check, you lose one duplicity mark. You may spend a duplicity mark to cast one of your known selected spells by spending a spell slot of the same level or higher. Each day when you regain uses of your spells, you lose any unused duplicity marks.
