Bravado											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																											PRESKILL:1,Bluff=5																												DESC:Use Bluff to demoralize foes.																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.57								BENEFIT:You may make a Bluff check to demoralize foes, as per the Intimidate skill. You may only attempt this 1/day for any given opponent. If you fail your attempt, the foe gains a +1 morale bonus to attack rolls against you for 1 round. If you fail by 5 or more, the morale bonus lasts for an additional 1d4 rounds.
Bushwhack											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																											PRESKILL:2,Perception=5,Stealth=5																										DESC:Conceal allies with Stealth.																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.57								BENEFIT:As a full round action, you may help an adjacent ally to conceal himself advantageously. The ally uses your Stealth check rather than his own, for as long as the ally remains where you placed him and takes no actions.
Catch!											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deceitful															PRESKILL:2,Bluff=1,Intimidate=1																										DESC:Toss an object to a foe, in hopes he'll catch it and drop his weapons.																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.57								BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can toss a small, non-weapon item at a target within 20 ft. while firmly shouting for them to catch it. You may make a Bluff check against the target's CMD. If your check succeeds, the target reflexively catches the item, dropping any held item to do so. The following conditions impose a cumulative -5 penalty to your Bluff check for each that applies: the target is threatened or in danger from you or your allies; you are not speaking a language understood by the target; or the target has more levels or hit dice than you. This feat does not work on any target that has seen this trick being used within the past 24 hours.
Cloak Fighting										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																											PRESKILL:1,Perform (Dance)=1								PREWEAPONPROF:1,Flail (Dire),Flail,Flail (Heavy),Nunchaku,Chain (Spiked),Whip							DESC:Use a cloak to gain concealment as a move action.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.58								BENEFIT:When you have a cloak in one hand, as a move action you may make a Perform (Dance) check opposed by one opponent's Perception or Sense Motive check (whichever is better for the opponent). If you win the opposed check, you gain 20%% concealment from that opponent until your next turn.
Double Bluff										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deceitful																																														DESC:Create a new Bluff to explain a failed Bluff.																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.59								BENEFIT:When you fail a Bluff check to fool someone, you can attempt a double-bluff. This requires you to develop some story by which you admit your first bluff was a lie, but explain it away as part of a new lie. This second attempt is at only a -2 penalty, instead of the normal -10 penalty for a second effort to deceive. If your second attempt fails, no third attempt is possible, regardless of what strategem you employ.
Established Persona									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																											PRESKILL:1,Disguise=2																						DEFINE:EstPersonaBonus|0		DESC:Gain bonuses to pass yourself off as a specific persona.											BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Established Persona|TL/2								BONUS:VAR|EstPersonaBonus|4	BONUS:VAR|EstPersonaBonus|2|PREVARGTEQ:TL,10	SOURCEPAGE:p.59								BENEFIT:You have %1 well-established personas other than your own identity. These are roles you have crafted and maintained backstories for, and which you have used often enough that enquiries into them will find people who will confirm they exist. You gain a +%2 bonus to all Bluff and Disguise checks to pass as the persona and to Linguistics checks to make forgeries in support of the persona. You may replace an existing persona with a new one at every odd-numbered level.|TL/2|EstPersonaBonus
Extra Cohort										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Leadership																																														DESC:Gain an additional cohort.																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.60								BENEFIT:You gain an additional cohort from your Leadership feat. The maximum level of this cohort is %1. It otherwise gains experience and levels using the normal cohort rules.|TL-4
False Blow											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deceitful																								PRETOTALAB:1																				DESC:Use a fake attack to cover a Sleight of Hand check.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.61								BENEFIT:As a standard action, make a melee attack against a target. If you hit the target, you deal no weapon damage. You may instead make a Sleight of Hand check to remove one item from the creature even though it is aware of you and in combat.
Feign Death											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																											PRESKILL:1,Bluff=5			PRESTAT:1,CON=13																							DESC:Play dead.																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.61								BENEFIT:You can attempt to appear dead, slowing your heartrate and breathing considerably, blocking out reactions to pinpricks and similar stimuli, and lowering your body temperature. Entering this trance-like state is a standard action, and while maintaining it you are paralyzed. In this trance you can hold your breath for %1 minutes, which is also the maximum duration of your trance. You appear dead to all casual observers and may make a Bluff check (opposed by an examiner's Heal or Perception check, whichever is higher) to appear dead even to careful examination. If you ready an action to use this feat when you are next struck for damage, the attacker must make a Perception check opposed by your Bluff, or believe it has slain you.|CONSCORE
Grim Determination									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Self-Sufficient					!PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=1														PRETOTALAB:2																				DESC:Gain temporary hit points once a day.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.62								BENEFIT:1/day, as a swift action, you can call upon the deep reserve of your independence, unbolstered by prayers or arcane knowledge, to drive yourself onward despite your injuries. You gain %1d6 temporary hit points.|TL/2
Master Artificer										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=ItemCreation														PRESKILL:1,Craft=5																												DESC:+4 to checks to create items, create items faster.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.65								BENEFIT:You gain a +4 bonus to any skill check made to complete a magic item you are creating. You create magic items in half the normal hours per day. As long as the total time spent on item creation does not exceed 8 hours per day, you can accomplish multiple days work on an item in a single day.
Muffle											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Grapple,Improved Unarmed Strike																PRESTAT:1,DEX=13																							DESC:Silence the targets of your grapples.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.65								BENEFIT:When you successfully initiate a grapple, you muffle sounds made by your target until it breaks the grapple. While the target is free to cry out (or fulfil the verbal components of spellcasting), you suppress the sounds so it is difficult for even nearby creatures to hear those noises. You may make a Stealth check against any opponent not directly observing you to prevent the sounds and movement of the grapple from being noticed.
Patois											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																											PRESKILL:1,Linguistics=5		PRESTAT:1,INT=13																							DESC:Communicate in languages you don't know.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.66								BENEFIT:Whenever you encounter creatures speaking a language you don't know, you can attempt to communicate by using phrases and words from similar languages. This requires you to make a Linguistics check (DC 15) for each concept you try to convey or understand, and even then only simple concepts can be exchanged. (As a general rule, each check allows you to send and receive one idea that can be expressed with no more than 5 single-syllable words.)
Physical Adept										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Athletic							!PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=1																																				DESC:Gain an extra standard action.																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.66								BENEFIT:%1/day, you can take an extra standard action at the beginning or end of your round. This standard action must be used for a purely physical action such as making an attack, readying an item, moving, or trying to lift or break something.|1+TL/4
Resolute											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Iron Will																																														DESC:Reduce the level of most fear effects to shaken.																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.67								BENEFIT:Any time you would normally be cowering, frightened, or panicked, you are instead shaken for the same duration. You take only half the penalties from similar effects.
Self Delusion										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13																							DESC:Add Charisma to Will saves, rather than Wisdom.																					BONUS:SAVE|Will|CHA-WIS|PREVARGT:CHA,WIS														SOURCEPAGE:p.68								BENEFIT:You may add your Charisma modifier rather than your Wisdom modifier to your Will saving throw bonus.
Sensitive											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																											PRESKILL:1,Spellcraft=5																												DESC:Use Spellcraft rather than Perception to notice some magic effects and creatures.																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.68								BENEFIT:You may make a Spellcraft check in place of a Perception check to notice spells, spell effects, magic items, and creatures of the aberration, construct, dragon, fey, outsider, and undead types. If you beat the required DC to notice something with Spellcraft by 5, you learn what category of thing you have sensed (including its type if it is a creature).
Subtle											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																																										DESC:Your actions are difficult to notice.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.70								BENEFIT:When you make certain skill checks (Appraise and Escape Artist checks, Diplomacy checks to gather information, or Perception checks to notice fine details), subjects observing or interacting with you must make Sense Motive checks (opposed by whatever skill you are using) to realize you are doing anything other than engaging in casual conversation or observation.
Thieves' Cant										CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																							PRECSKILL:1,Bluff																																	DESC:Send and receive secret messages.																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.71								BENEFIT:Your subtle cunning improves your use of the Bluff skill to pass secret messages. You may attempt to pass a secret message of no more than 15 words as a free action once per round (rather than a full-round action) and characters other than the intended recipient take a -5 penalty to Sense Motive checks to intercept your message. Any time you attempt to send a secret message to an ally who has the Thieves' Cant feat, there is no chance of the message being misunderstood.
Wall Runner											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Acrobatic Steps,Nimble Moves																		PRESTAT:1,WIS=13																							DESC:Run up along walls.																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.72								BENEFIT:As long as you are no more than lightly encumbered and suffering an armor check penalty of no more than -1, you can take part of one move action each round to traverse a wall or other relatively smooth vertical surface if you begin and end your move on a horizontal surface. If you do not end your move on a horizontal surface, you fall prone, taking falling damage as appropriate. Treat the wall as a normal floor for the purpose of measuring your movement. Passing from floor to wall, or wall to floor, costs no movement; you can change surfaces freely. Opponents on the ground can make attacks of opportunity normally if you leave a threatened space.

